or folder name for batch installation
Input the file name of APK

# Workflow Configuration
- adb_path, e.g. "~/Library/Android/sdk/platform-tools/adb" - aapt_path, e.g. "~/Library/Android/sdk/build-tools/31.0.0/aapt" - apksigner_path, e.g. "~/Library/Android/sdk/build-tools/31.0.0/apksigner" - emulator_path, e.g. "~/Library/Android/sdk/emulator/emulator" - config_clipboard, set as 1 if needs copy output to clipboard,
# Usage
Use keyword "adb" to get quick access to:
- restart adb - connect/disconnect devices over WiFi - check connected devices - run any shell command to target device - check installed application to force stop, clear data, uninstall - install new APK or APKs with various options - take screenshot and/or copy to clipboard - open settings, dev tool, WiFi, applications, accessibility page - toggle debug layout and demo mode - advanced reboot - input key or text on device - and many more convenient functions
Use keyword "apk" to check the infomation of apk file and execute installation
Use keyword "apkf" to list all apk files of the front Finder window
Use keyword "avd" to list and start Android emulator
Use keyword "geny" to list and start Genymotion emulator
Full function list at:
https://github.com/zjn0505/adb-alfred
List apk files from current front Finder window
Hotkey to open select apk file
Please provide the path of adb executable
Path to your adb executable, e.g. ~/Library/Android/sdk/platform-tools/adb You may be able to check it in terminal with "which adb".
Please provide the path of aapt executable
Path to your aapt executable, e.g. ~/Library/Android/sdk/build-tools/31.0.0/aapt Used in the workflow to check apk file infomation. You may be able to check it in terminal with "which aapt"
Please provide the path of aapt executable

Path to your apksigner executable e.g. ~/Library/Android/sdk/build-tools/31.0.0/apksigner Used in the workflow to check apk file signature. You may be able to check it in terminal with "which apksigner"
Please provide the path of emulator executable
Path to your apksigner executable. e.g. ~/Library/Android/sdk/emulator/emulator Used to manage and launch Android emulators You may be able to check it in terminal with "which emulator".
